The paper discusses the issue of bias in machine learning, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also touches on the impact of biased data on machine learning models, which is relevant to the subfield of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social implications of technology (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses interactive plots to visualize the bias learned from synthetic data, which could be relevant to the subfield of cybernetics (cs.CY).
